omething approaching the British political culture, but the wounds opened by the Revolution could not readily be healed. A more or less complete acceptance of the civil disagreement that was the spirit of the British model had to await the Fifth Republic.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aHISTORY / Europe / France.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077357718340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773577183423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773577183/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles